<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 8:58PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Person and northern
Granville Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 858 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cluster Springs, or near Virgilina, moving south at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Oxford, Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Bushy Fork, Hyco Lake, Moriah,
Mayo Reservoir, Hyco Marina and Berea.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
